args:
The party defeats the fiends and makes the
acquaintance of several choir members,
including young Elias. Though the present
crisis has been averted, the recital cannot
begin until safety is assured, so the prince
promises to take care of the fiends and departs.
You guys are lifesavers! And so strong!\nWho in the world ARE you?
I'm the seventh prince of the Kingdom of\nAlberia, {player_name}.
Goodness, that IS fancy! I had no idea you\nwere that prince I keep hearing about.
We can't very well hold a recital if the\npeople here might be attacked by fiends.
Indeed. We may have no choice but\nto cancel.
But everyone practiced so hard.\nIt means everything to them!
You guys can't give up because of a few\nlousy fiends. You've been rehearsing all\nyear for this night!
If the fiends could be culled and the safety\nof everyone involved guaranteed, would\nyou be able to hold your recital?
I see no reason why not. But alas, our\nchoir is rather short of members who\nknow how to deal with fiends.
Then let us take care of that.
*sniff* And then...we can have the recital?
We'll make sure of it. Just hold on for a\nlittle bit longer, all right?
That's good to hear. But what about you,\nMariti?
As the owner of the choir, I'd like very\nmuch to see this happen...
So, yes! Defeat those nasty fiends so we\ncan all sing our hearts out in celebration!
I-I'm fine! I was just clearing my throat.\nPlease leave me alone.
Elias! Your distinguished colleague Vixel\nis merely worried about you.
Distinguished colleague? You mean this\nperson who gave up singing?
Are you still worried about that kid after\nhow he talked to you?
Well, he's not wrong that I abandoned my\nsinging career. But in any case, please\nallow me to help you all.
Now let's finish our fiend hunt and get this\nperformance off the ground!
*cough* A-HEM! A-A-AAAAHEM.\n...Nope. My throat still feels weird.\nAnd to make it worse, I can't sleep.
(By tomorrow, I might not be able to even\nsing with my normal voice anymore...)
I WANT IT ALL TO GO AWAY!
(That dream yesterday was so strange.\nAll I want to do is forget it, and I can't!)
(＂Go away＂ can't be referring to the choir,\nright? ...No, I'd never think that!)
(I mean, I'd never want the choir to go\naway just because I might have to leave\nit...right?)
There's some kind of commotion outside.\n...Oh!
I wonder if those people are okay.\n...AHEM! *hack*
How many of these dang things ARE\nthere, anyway?!
If they manage to get into town, it's going\nto be bad news. Push them back into the\nmountains!
